{"_id":"f0c582d0-aa46-11ea-bcd9-83d6a42daef7","postId":"2009_05_detection-of-half-open-dropped-f127b1d1-2c83-3dd0-9e4b-214360c6e878","postUri":"https://blog.stephencleary.com/2009/05/detection-of-half-open-dropped.html","replyTo":"8af51d90-aa40-11ea-a07c-4f8466a19c21","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"23448e78d187fba56d8bc263081ac5d8","authorName":"Stephen Cleary","authorUri":"https://stephencleary.com","message":"To detect half-open connections, your software just needs to periodically send noop messages. How frequently you send them is based on how quickly you need to detect a dropped connection, which is based on what you define \"real-time\" to be. I've found that for most applications, a period of 1 second is sufficient, but some systems require a smaller resolution.","date":"2020-06-09T11:47:05.414Z"}